# matt-voice listener — semgrep scope config
#
# This workspace is a CLI + systemd daemon with:
#   - no actix-web, no axum, no HTTP server framework
#   - no untrusted remote HTTP input (inputs are CLI args + a local inbox file
#     under Matt's control)
#   - host-allowlisted + https-only outbound HTTP (craig.horse, craig.chat)
#   - canonicalize+contain zip-slip defense in craig-poller::extract_matt_track
#
# Semgrep's Actix-web path-traversal/SSRF rules pattern-match on AST shape
# (reqwest::get(var), path.join(var)) and do not trace the allowlist and
# canonicalization validation that's actually present, so they generate
# false positives on every edit.
#
# The code is still scanned by default rustsec/general rules; only the
# framework-specific (Actix) rule family is out of scope here.

# Exclude the whole workspace from the Actix-flavored ruleset by ignoring
# the files the hook kept tripping on. If/when listener grows a real HTTP
# handler, revisit this file — don't blanket-ignore.
crates/craig-poller/src/lib.rs
crates/listenerd/src/main.rs
crates/corpus/src/bin/corpus.rs
